(function(fnUtils, CMP) {
const deferLoadTime = 5000;
const readyForThirdPartyTrackingEvent = new CustomEvent('readyForThirdPartyTracking', { bubbles: true });
const readyForThirdPartyTracking = fnUtils.once(function() {
window.dataLayer.push({event: 'readyForThirdPartyTracking'});
window.dispatchEvent(readyForThirdPartyTrackingEvent);
});
const readyForDeferredScriptsEvent = new CustomEvent('readyForDeferredScripts', { bubbles: true });
const readyForDeferredScripts = fnUtils.once(function() {
window.dataLayer.push({event: 'readyForDeferredScripts'});
window.dispatchEvent(readyForDeferredScriptsEvent);
});
const hasTargetingConsentHandler = function() {
const hasConsent = CMP.hasTargetingConsent();
if (hasConsent) {
readyForThirdPartyTracking();
}
// Trigger the readyForDeferredScripts if consent is given
// or if the user has closed the banner(AlertBox) which exists for EU
// or if the user optin consent is not required, which applies for non gdpr locations
if (hasConsent || CMP.isAlertBoxClosed() || !CMP.isOptInConsent()) {
readyForDeferredScripts();
}
return hasConsent;
};
const purposeOneConsentHandler = async function() {
const hasPurposeOneConsent = await CMP.hasPurposeOneConsent();
if (hasPurposeOneConsent) {
readyForThirdPartyTracking();
}
if (hasPurposeOneConsent || CMP.isAlertBoxClosed()) {
readyForDeferredScripts();
}
return hasPurposeOneConsent;
};
const onRequiredDomEvent = fnUtils.once(function() {
if (!CMP) {
readyForThirdPartyTracking();
readyForDeferredScripts();
return;
}
const handler = CMP.supportsTCData() ? purposeOneConsentHandler : hasTargetingConsentHandler;
if (!CMP.isLoading()) {
handler();
}
CMP.onConsentChange(handler);
});
[
['adRendered', onRequiredDomEvent],
['beforeunload', onRequiredDomEvent],
['load', function() { setTimeout(onRequiredDomEvent, deferLoadTime); }]
].forEach(function(event) {
window.addEventListener(event[0], event[1], { once: true });
});

<p class="article-subheading text-body-100">I found this pancake recipe in my Grandma's recipe book. Judging from the weathered look of this recipe card, this was a family favorite.</p>

<div id="mm-recipes-intro__content_1-0" class="comp mm-recipes-intro__content mntl-sc-page mntl-block" data-sc-sticky-offset="190" data-sc-ad-label-height="24" data-sc-ad-track-spacing="100" data-sc-min-track-height="250" data-sc-max-track-height="600" data-sc-breakpoint="50em" data-sc-load-immediate="1" data-sc-content-positions="[1, 1250, 1550, 1950, 2350, 2750, 3150, 3550, 3950]" data-bind-scroll-on-start="true"><p id="mntl-sc-block_1-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> Perfect pancakes are easier to make than you think. This pancake recipe produces thick, fluffy, and all-around delicious pancakes with just a few ingredients that are probably already in your kitchen (and it&#39;s so much better than the boxed stuff).
</p>
<div id="mntl-sc-block_2-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block"></div>
<span class="heading-toc" id="toc-how-to-make-pancakes"></span><h2 id="mntl-sc-block_3-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block allrecipes-sc-block-heading mntl-sc-block-heading"> <span class="mntl-sc-block-heading__text"> How to Make Pancakes </span> </h2>
<p id="mntl-sc-block_4-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> You&#39;ll find a detailed ingredient list and step-by-step instructions in the recipe below, but let&#39;s go over the basics:
</p>
<div id="mntl-sc-block_5-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block"></div>
<h3 id="mntl-sc-block_6-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block allrecipes-sc-block-subheading mntl-sc-block-subheading"> <span class="mntl-sc-block-subheading__text"> Pancake Ingredients </span> </h3>
<p id="mntl-sc-block_7-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> You likely already have everything you need to make this pancake recipe. If not, here&#39;s what to add to your grocery list:
</p>
<div id="mntl-sc-block_8-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block"></div>
<p id="mntl-sc-block_9-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> <strong>· Flour</strong>: This homemade pancake recipe starts with all-purpose flour.<br/><strong>· Baking powder</strong>: Baking powder, a leavener, is the secret to fluffy pancakes.<br/><strong>· Sugar</strong>: Just a tablespoon of white sugar is all you&#39;ll need for subtly sweet pancakes.<br/><strong>· Salt</strong>: A pinch of salt will enhance the overall flavor without making your pancakes taste salty.<br/><strong>· Milk</strong> and <strong>butter</strong>: Milk and butter add moisture and richness to the pancakes.<br/><strong>· Egg</strong>: A whole egg lends even more moisture. Plus, it helps bind the pancake batter together.
</p>
<div id="mntl-sc-block_10-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block"></div>
<h3 id="mntl-sc-block_11-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block allrecipes-sc-block-subheading mntl-sc-block-subheading"> <span class="mntl-sc-block-subheading__text"> How to Make Pancakes From Scratch </span> </h3>
<p id="mntl-sc-block_12-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> It&#39;s not hard to make homemade pancakes — you just need a good recipe. That&#39;s where we come in! You&#39;ll find the step-by-step recipe below, but here&#39;s a brief overview of what you can expect:
</p>
<div id="mntl-sc-block_13-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block"></div>
<p id="mntl-sc-block_14-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> 1. Sift the dry ingredients together.<br/>2. Make a well, then add the wet ingredients. Stir to combine.<br/>3. Scoop the batter onto a hot griddle or pan.<br/>4. Cook for two to three minutes, then flip.<br/>5. Continue cooking until brown on both sides.
</p>
<div id="mntl-sc-block_15-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block"></div>
<h3 id="mntl-sc-block_16-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block allrecipes-sc-block-subheading mntl-sc-block-subheading"> <span class="mntl-sc-block-subheading__text"> When to Flip Pancakes </span> </h3>
<p id="mntl-sc-block_17-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> Your pancake will tell you when it&#39;s ready to flip. Wait until bubbles start to form on the top and the edges look dry and set. This will usually take about two to three minutes on each side.
</p>
<div id="mntl-sc-block_18-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block"></div>
<span class="heading-toc" id="toc-how-to-reheat-pancakes"></span><h2 id="mntl-sc-block_19-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block allrecipes-sc-block-heading mntl-sc-block-heading"> <span class="mntl-sc-block-heading__text"> How to Reheat Pancakes </span> </h2>
<p id="mntl-sc-block_20-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> Store leftover pancakes in an airtight container in the fridge for about a week. Refrain from adding toppings (such as syrup) until right before you serve them so the pancakes don&#39;t get soggy.
</p>
<div id="mntl-sc-block_21-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block"></div>
<figure id="mntl-sc-block_22-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block allrecipes-sc-block-image mntl-sc-block-image mntl-sc-block-image--no-theme no-theme figure-landscape figure-high-res"> <div class="figure-media">
<div class="img-placeholder" style="padding-bottom:66.6%;">

<figcaption id="mntl-figure-caption_1-0" class="comp mntl-figure-caption text-utility-100 figure-article-caption"> <span class="figure-article-caption-owner">angela</span>
</figcaption></figure>
<span class="heading-toc" id="toc-can-you-save-pancake-batter"></span><h2 id="mntl-sc-block_23-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block allrecipes-sc-block-heading mntl-sc-block-heading"> <span class="mntl-sc-block-heading__text"> Can You Save Pancake Batter? </span> </h2>
<p id="mntl-sc-block_24-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> Don&#39;t let leftover pancake batter go to waste! Store the batter in an airtight container in the fridge for up to two days. If you plan to keep it longer than that, it&#39;s best to freeze the batter.
</p>
<div id="mntl-sc-block_25-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block"></div>
<span class="heading-toc" id="toc-can-you-freeze-pancakes"></span><h2 id="mntl-sc-block_26-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block allrecipes-sc-block-heading mntl-sc-block-heading"> <span class="mntl-sc-block-heading__text"> Can You Freeze Pancakes? </span> </h2>
<p id="mntl-sc-block_27-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> Yes, you can freeze pancakes and pancake batter.
</p>
<div id="mntl-sc-block_28-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block"></div>
<p id="mntl-sc-block_29-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> <strong>· To freeze cooked pancakes</strong>: Allow the pancakes to cool completely, then arrange them in a single layer on a baking sheet (make sure the edges aren&#39;t touching). Flash freeze for a few hours or up to overnight. Reheat in an oven set to 350 degrees F until warmed through.<br/><strong>· To freeze pancake batter</strong>: Ladle the pancake batter in serving size portions into freezer bags, then wrap the bags in foil. Freeze flat for up to one month. Thaw in the refrigerator overnight.
</p>
<div id="mntl-sc-block_30-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block"></div>
<span class="heading-toc" id="toc-allrecipes-community-tips-and-praise"></span><h2 id="mntl-sc-block_31-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block allrecipes-sc-block-heading mntl-sc-block-heading"> <span class="mntl-sc-block-heading__text"> Allrecipes Community Tips and Praise </span> </h2>
<p id="mntl-sc-block_32-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> "This recipe is one to hand down to your grandkids," raves <a href="https://www.allrecipes.com/cook/6561257" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="1">ashleyalbertine</a>. "Fluffy and delicious. Haven't bought a box of pancake mix in months! Just add a bit of vanilla and poof! Magic."
</p>
<div id="mntl-sc-block_33-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block"></div>
<p id="mntl-sc-block_34-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> "Perfect," according to <a href="https://www.allrecipes.com/cook/15132461" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="1">Laura W</a>. "Delicious! If you're looking for some thick, hearty pancakes these are the ones to make! Made them exactly as the recipe states and then added mini-chocolate chips to each cake as they were on the frying pan (before flipping)."
</p>
<div id="mntl-sc-block_35-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block"></div>
<p id="mntl-sc-block_36-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> "I made this recipe exactly as written...the kids were eating them off the plate faster than I could cook them," says <a href="https://www.allrecipes.com/cook/6018059" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="1">aellis1970</a>. "They are so delicious, they were eaten without syrup."
</p>

<div id="mm-recipes-steps_1-0" class="comp mm-recipes-steps mntl-block"><h2 id="mm-recipes-steps__heading_1-0" class="comp mm-recipes-steps__heading mntl-text-block">Directions</h2>
<div id="mm-recipes-steps__content_1-0" class="comp mm-recipes-steps__content mntl-sc-page mntl-block"><OL id="mntl-sc-block_39-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-startgroup mntl-sc-block-group--OL">
<LI id="mntl-sc-block_40-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-startgroup mntl-sc-block-group--LI">
<p id="mntl-sc-block_41-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> Sift flour, baking powder, sugar, and salt together in a large bowl. Make a well in the center and add milk, melted butter, and egg; mix until smooth.
</p>
<div id="mntl-sc-block_42-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block"></div>
</LI>
<LI id="mntl-sc-block_44-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-startgroup mntl-sc-block-group--LI">
<p id="mntl-sc-block_45-0" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html"> Heat a lightly oiled griddle or pan over medium-high heat. Pour or scoop the batter onto the griddle, using approximately 1/4 cup for each pancake; cook until bubbles form and the edges are dry, about 2 to 3 minutes. Flip and cook until browned on the other side. Repeat with remaining batter.
</p>

<span id="ugc-review__chip--text_8-0" class="comp ugc-review__chip--text mntl-text-block">Great flavors</span></span>
<span id="ugc-review__chip-wrapper_9-0" class="comp ugc-review__chip-wrapper mntl-block"><svg class="icon ugc-icon-check-circle ugc-review__chip--icon"

<use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ugc-icon-check-circle" href="#ugc-icon-check-circle"></use>

<span id="ugc-review__chip--text_9-0" class="comp ugc-review__chip--text mntl-text-block">Easy to follow</span></span></div>
<div id="ugc-review__text_3-0" class="comp ugc-review__text mntl-text-block">Great classic, super easy and quick to make too. Made many times as is but with vanilla extract. In this picture, made it with 50/50 white flour and whole wheat flour, added 1tsp vanilla extract, 1/4tsp cinnamon powder, substituted milk with buttermilk (just add 1tbsp white vinegar to room temp milk and let sit for 5-10minutes), and left out salt. Sift the dry ingredients a few times then whisk everything together until just combined. Pancakes were fluffy and tasted great. This tweaked recipe will be a family staple ❤️</div></div></div></div></div> </div>
</div>
